Version 0.2.1 (2026-06-19)
* Install command: fully implemented with recursive dependency resolution,
  MAKEFS build execution, and lfspkg package registration.
* Rebuild command: support --stale (auto-detect packages whose dependencies
  have been upgraded), --all, and per-package modes.  Automatic cascade
  rebuild of reverse dependencies after any rebuild.
* Upgrade command: compare installed versions against repository index
  and upgrade out-of-date packages with full cascade.
* List command: query lfspkg database for installed packages.
* Link against lfspkg static library for package database operations.
* lfspkg: built_deps tracking records each dependency's version at build
  time; find_stale_packages() detects packages needing rebuild.

Version 0.2.0 (2026-06-05)
* Configuration system: layered config from /etc/qp.conf and
  ~/.config/qp/qp.conf with KEY=VALUE format.
* Update command: clone or pull the qur package repository
  and regenerate the package index from all MAKEFS scripts.
* Search command: case-insensitive keyword search across
  package names and descriptions from the local index.
* Build system: ignore automake parallel test harness artifacts.

Version 0.1.3 (2026-05-29)
* MAKEFS parser: two-pass state machine that parses PKGBUILD-style build
  description files.  Handles variable definitions with $(VAR)/${VAR}
  expansion, [package.X] sub-package sections, [trigger] sections, shell
  function body collection (prepare/build/check/package/package_X), and
  heredoc multi-line strings (<<TERM ... TERM).  Function bodies are
  preserved raw for later shell execution — no expansion is applied.
* Comprehensive test suite: 18 test cases covering basic parsing, full
  multi-package example, chained variable expansion, heredoc, function
  bodies, brace expansion tolerance, backslash continuation, CRLF
  handling, comments, duplicate keys, and error conditions.

Version 0.1.2 (2026-05-29)
* Subcommand framework with eight commands: search, install, remove,
  rebuild, list, update, register, unregister (all are stubs).
* Internationalization: gettext support with Chinese (zh_CN) translation.
* Utility module with classic fork+exec helper for subprocess execution.
* Command-line argument parsing and dispatch via table-driven lookup.
* po/ directory with translation infrastructure (POT, PO, LINGUAS).
Version 0.1.1 (2026-05-26)
* Build system: add GitHub Actions CI with automatic distcheck and release.
Version 0.1.0 (2026-05-26)
* Initial project skeleton with autotools build system.
* Basic hello world program for testing.
* Trivial test suite with make check.
